ds to be converted to radians. The frequency is 0.55Hz. \n\nThe simulation time (time_max) is calculated as 5 divided by the frequency. So 5/0.55 ≈ 9.09 seconds. \n\nFor the particle spacing (dp), the minimum dimension is the diameter (1m). The rule is dp = min(L, W, H)/50. Here, the diameter is 1m, so dp = 1/50 = 0.02m. That's within the 0.005-0.05m range. \n\nThe geometry part: since it's a cylinder, I need to create a box for the tank and then use a shape command to make it cylindrical. The fluid fill is 25%, so the fluid box's height is 0.25m. \n\nThe motion parameters: amplitude is 3 degrees converted to radians. The formula for amplitude in radians is degrees * π/180. So 3 * π/180 ≈ 0.0523 radians. \n\nThe XML structure needs to include the cylindrical tank. The commands section should have a drawbox for the tank and then a shape command to convert it into a cylinder. The fluid is another drawbox with the specified height. \n\nI also need to set the motion parameters correctly. The mvrotsinu element should have the frequency and amplitude. The frequency is 0.55Hz, and the amplitude is 0.0523 radians. \n\nCheck the parameters section for DualSPHysics settings. The boundary condition is set to 2 (mDBC), and other parameters like kernel, viscosity, etc., are set as per standard. \n\nMake sure the gravity is set correctly (z=-9.81). The fluid density is 1000 kg/m³ by default. \n\nFinally, verify all the parameters and ensure the XML structure is correct. The tank's dimensions in the XML should reflect the horizontal cylinder, and the motion is correctly applied as a pitch movement.\n","done":true,"done_reason":"stop","context":[151644,8948,271,64795,82528,33704,79207,105,17380,144108,3759,385,927,287,8,60716,129150,56419,51588,15235,124685,134619,94152,28626,78952,624,55054,26699,131958,140577,31079,142163,17877,33659,4592,39,17243,348,20,13,19,11874,3315,120,222,12802,24897,67629,17380,137352,46319,65238,60838,624,10609,72553,61126,91145,13,133828,129835,91605,51